Then Taiwan. Then South Korea, Then Singapore.
the pride with which people talk about not wearing masks wouldn't go over that well in the PRC which has a smoking hot economy and almost no covid and they wear masks. 1.2 billion not anecdotal.

The key thing is to find out, by testing, who has it before he can spread it. Next, social distance and contact trace. Then if you can't social distance wear a mask. That's the pecking order. Mask is last but it can help when the rest fail. Nothing's perfect. It's better

The Chinese beat us in large part because they wear masks, contact trace and have rigor and discipline. How can people not see that this happened. Tariffs meant nothing versus the discipline they showed by masks, contact trace.
